hilanthropist founder identified poverty, alcohol, drugs and gambling among the social evils of his time, the Joseph Rowntree Foundation initiated a major consultation among leading thinkers, activists and commentators, as well as the wider public. The findings have now been brought together in this fascinating book. Individual contributors range across the political spectrum but the book also reports the results from a web survey and consultation with groups whose voices are less often heard. The results suggest that while some evils - like poverty - endure as undisputed causes of social harm, more recent sources of social misery, such as an alleged rise in selfish consumerism and a perceived decline in personal responsibility and family commitment, attract controversy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSocial problemszGreat Britain. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aBailey, Shaun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBauman, Zygmunt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrowne, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCreegan, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrayling, A.C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris, Jose, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKinsella, Rachel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawson, Neal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMinton, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMount, Ferdinand, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMowlam, Alice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeuberger, Baro